						               													<description>Fist Fight: The Card Game is a fast-paced, 1-on-1 card game based off of the action of old-school arcade fighting cabinets.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Two players simultaneously lay down cards from their hands and try to reduce their opponents hit points to 0. First person to do so wins the round, first to win 2 rounds wins the game. Rounds should last around 60 seconds.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are attack, block, throw, and counter cards, all of which need to be played strategically to maximize the damage a player can do to their opponent, without taking too much damage of their own.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Predicting what your opponent might play and making a decision on what to do within seconds adds an arcade feel to the game; there isn't always time to think things over, sometimes you just have to throw down a card and hope it works, we call that our version of button mashing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Whether played with a single opponent, or against a group of people rotating in and out, Fist Fight will provide hours of the high-energy entertainment.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
